text: Mirny () is a rural locality (a settlement) in Solyansky Selsoviet, Narimanovsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 514 as of 2010. There are 41 streets. == Geography == It is located 9 km from Astrakhan, 35 km from Narimanov. == References == Category:Rural localities in Narimanovsky District
title: Mirny, Astrakhan Oblast
